[30;1m98 | [0m[35m                        - step 1 : We parse the choices between ([A-Z])s then try to find these choi[0m
[30;1m99 | [0m[35m                        - step 2 : We parse the choice with regex :[\s]*([A-?]), where ? varies by n[0m
[30;1m100 | [0m[35m        group_select: Selects the (group_select)th match from the findall result.[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m        ignore_case: Ignores the case during step 1 matching[0m

[30;1m145 | [0m[35mInstruction-Following Eval (IFEval) for large language models. IFEval is a[0m
[30;1m146 | [0m[35mstraightforward and easy-to-reproduce evaluation benchmark. It focuses on a set[0m
[30;1m147 | [0m[35mof "verifiable instructions" such as "write in more than 400 words" and[0m

[30;1m51 | [0m[35m      x^2 + c does not have roots in Z_3. That is x^2 + c != 0 for every x in Z_3.[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m      If c = 0, then x^2 + c = x^2 has root 0. If c = 1 then x^2 + c = x^2 + 1 = 0[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m      + 1 for x = 0, 1 + 1 = 2 for x = 1 and 1 + 1 = 2 for x = 2, hence x^2 + 1 does[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m      not have any roots. For c = 2 the polynomial x^2 + 2 has two roots at x = 1[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m      and x = 2. Hence Z_3[x]/(x^2 + c) is a field if and only if c = 1. The answer[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m      is (B).'[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35mtag: mmlu_flan_cot_fewshot_stem[0m
